                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5494.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Acapulco</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Acapulco</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-14T15:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1912—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Rebel leader Padilla controls all coast region to north of Acapulco. All
                    Government troops have retreated to Acapulco.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry K. Pangburn.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
